cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.PL

Reasoning: 

- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper is about Network Function Virtualization (NFV) which is a networking concept. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of NFV platforms which can be considered as a system. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as NFV platforms involve distributed computing. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category as the paper focuses more on software design choices rather than hardware architecture. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a less likely category as the paper does not primarily focus on programming languages.
